		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">Environmental effects of China's solar photovoltaic industry during2011e2016: A life cycle assessment approach</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">2011-2016年中国太阳能光伏产业生命周期环境影响评价</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">After the melt, solidifi-cation and anneal of solar grade multi-Si in quartz crucible, the ingot will be produced</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">在石英坩埚中对太阳能级多晶硅进行熔融、凝固和退火处理后，可生产出铸锭</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The solar grade multi-Si ingot casting process described is used for the manufacturing of multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) cells, which are a primary component in the construction of solar photovoltaic (PV) modules. These modules are then assembled to create solar PV systems capable of converting solar energy into electricity. In this specific case, the ingots are utilized to produce cells for a 1 kWp solar PV system, comprised of five 200 W modules with each module containing 54 multi-Si cells measuring 156*156 mm2 with an efficiency of 16%. The process is relevant for the solar energy industry, specifically in the context of the life cycle environmental impact assessment of the Chinese solar photovoltaic industry between 2011 and 2016.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">本工艺所描述的太阳能级多晶硅铸锭过程是用于制造多晶硅电池的关键步骤，这些电池是组装太阳能光伏模块的主要组成部分。再将这些模块组合起来，创建能将太阳能转换为电能的太阳能光伏系统。在此案例中，铸锭用于生产1千瓦峰值（kWp）太阳能光伏系统的电池，该系统由五个200瓦模块组成，每个模块包含54片尺寸为156*156毫米、效率为16%的多晶硅电池。该过程适用于太阳能行业，特别是在2011至2016年期间中国太阳能光伏产业生命周期环境影响评估的背景下。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="12a1e0b7-2f33-c1ae-b57b-afe1edf94591" uri="../sources/12a1e0b7-2f33-c1ae-b57b-afe1edf94591.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">BXlrbJ3VWokXszxfEQecQzbrnxg.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
